    title: 'Programmatically navigate using React router',
    body: '{"blocks":[{"key":"6v82q","text":"With react-router I can use the Link element to create links which are natively handled by react router.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1qoth","text":"I see internally it calls this.context.transitionTo(...).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"490f2","text":"I want to do a navigation. Not from a link, but from a dropdown selection (as an example). How can I do this in code? What is this.context?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8qm19","text":"I saw the Navigation mixin, but can I do this without mixins?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}',
