    title: 'How do I add TypeScript to my existing Vite (React) application?',
    body: "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"csvhb\",\"text\":\"I have an existing react app which I created using Vite. I used the react template in Vite-\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"3aji5\",\"text\":\"yarn create vite my-react-app --template react\",\"type\":\"code\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"4s75i\",\"text\":\"As the project progressed, it seemed a good idea to include TypeScript for stricter type checking. I had earlier included TypeScript in one of my existing projects using create-react-app with the help of this clear documentation. I tried incorporating the same in my Vite app. I executed the following code in my terminal -\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"b8mvd\",\"text\":\"yarn add typescript @types/node @types/react @types/react-dom @types/jest\",\"type\":\"code\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"8urm2\",\"text\":\"I renamed my .jsx files to .tsx and my vite.config.js to vite.config.ts and restarted my vite server.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"6fssf\",\"text\":\"But to my utter dismay, the app stopped working. I couldn't find any documentation in the vite docs for adding TypeScript to an existing app. I also searched in the Vite Github community, but couldn't find anything relatable there. I couldn't find anything related to this on the web too. Most of the stuff is on CRA and Typescript.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"bbda\",\"text\":\"Any help on this would be appreciated. Thanks!\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
